    <body>
        <h2 style="text-align: center; color:white; background-color: black;padding: 20px; margin:-20px;">
        freecodecamp - file metadata</h2>

<div class = "container">
    <div style="text-align: center;border: 2px solid black; margin-top: 50px; background-color: #C6C7C4;
    margin: 0; position: absolute; top: 50%; left: 50%; -ms-transform: translate(-50%, -50%); transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    -webkit-box-shadow: -27px 25px 10px -7px rgba(0,0,0,1);
    -moz-box-shadow: -27px 25px 10px -7px rgba(0,0,0,1); 
    box-shadow: -27px 25px 10px -7px rgba(0,0,0,1);">
        <ol>
            <h3>User Stories:</h3>
            <li>I can submit a form object that includes a file upload.</li>
            <li>The from file input field has the "name" attribute set to "upfile". We rely on this in testing.</li>
            <li>When I submit something, I will receive the file name, and size in bytes within the JSON response.</li>
        </ol>
        <h3>Usage:</h3>
        <p>Please Upload a File ... </p>
        <hr>
    
        <div style="text-align: center;margin-top: 30px;">
                <form action="/upload" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <input type ="file" id="upfile" name="upfile">
                        <input type="submit" value="upload">
                    </div>
                </form>
            </div>
    </div>
</div>


